cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with linguistic typology and proposes a computational model for discovering typological implications.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the proposed model uses Bayesian inference, a common technique in AI.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves learning patterns from data.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper involves analyzing and processing large amounts of linguistic data.
